---Attribute---
An element can have attributes

Attribute
- characteristic of element
- provide info about element
- specified in start tag
- follows name/value pairs e.g name="value"
<tagname attributename="attributevalue">
    Content
</tagname>
- always quote atrribute value

Examples

lang in html
<html lang="en-US">

style in p
<p style="color:#e8d7c9; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'; font-size: 14pt;">Hello, I'm Vanessa! Welcome to my first web portfolio!</p>

src in img
alt in img
class in img
width and height in img
<img src="/img/vanessaprofile.png" alt="Picture of Vanessa" class="center">


href in a
<a href="image-gallery.html">Gallery</a>
href is the attribute of element, a

2 Ways to specify URL with the href attribute:
Relative URL - relative to the current HTML or root of the website
<a href="image-gallery.html">Gallery</a>

Absolute URL - located on another website 
<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/vanessa-ho-6838b5211/">LinkedIn</a>